
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a target node. It retrieves nodes specified by arguments such as [limit], [offset], [order], and [direction] using the [get-nodes] slot, and adds them to the [data.read] node. The code effectively aggregates these argument nodes into the [data.read] node for further processing or manipulation.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
